Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and season with salt and pepper. Cook until browned all over and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the chicken has about 5 minutes left, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @chives{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (use scissors if easier).

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the garlic to the pan and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @water{150%ml}, @miso paste{15%g} and @wild mushroom paste{15%g}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the cooked pasta, @butter{20%g} and half the chives.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

Share the creamy miso pasta out between your #bowls{}.

Finish by sprinkling over the remaining chives. Enjoy!